# D365 F&O Batch and Business Logic

Microsoft source: [Process automation](https://learn.microsoft.com/dynamics365/fin-ops-core/dev-itpro/process-automation/run-process)

## Core rules

- New code: **SysOperationServiceController** over `RunBaseBatch`
- Short TTS; checkpoints; idempotent chunks
- ≤1000 batch tasks per job
- Version `pack`/`unpack` when parameters change
- Labels for all Infolog messages; surface `CLRError` to Infolog

## Scenarios and recommendations

### New scheduled export / import / calculation

**Recommend:** Controller + service + contract/data contract classes; menu item + batch privilege; SysTest on service with ATL data.

**Avoid:** New class extending `RunBaseBatch` for greenfield integration.

### Long-running job (100k+ records)

**Recommend:** Chunk by RecId or batch group; **commit per chunk**; store checkpoint RecId; design retry from checkpoint.

**Avoid:** Single `ttsbegin`/`ttscommit` wrapping entire loop.

### Many parallel batch tasks

**Recommend:** ≤1000 tasks; each task processes a **set** (chunk), not one record per task.

**Avoid:** 5000 tasks each updating one row.

### Change batch job parameters after deployment

**Recommend:** Increment version constant; `unpack` handles **prior and current** pack format.

**Avoid:** Remove `conPeek` index without version branch — breaks in-flight jobs.

### User-facing failure in batch

**Recommend:** Outermost `try`/`catch`; `error("@MyPubLabel:Failed")`; retry `UpdateConflict`/`Deadlock` appropriately.

**Avoid:** `throw Exception::Error`; silent catch; lost CLRError message.

### Caching reference data in batch

**Recommend:** Session-scoped temp tables or bounded cache; table cache where Microsoft documents it.

**Avoid:** Unbounded static `Map` holding table data across batch tasks.

## SysOperation vs RunBase

```xpp
// BAD — new integration export
class MyPub_ExportBatch extends RunBaseBatch
{
    public void run() { /* ... */ }
}

// GOOD
class MyPub_ExportController extends SysOperationServiceController
{
    public static void main(Args _args)
    {
        new MyPub_ExportController().startOperation();
    }
}
```

